You're missing the **`BindingContext`**. Without it, the `{Binding}` expressions have no source object to pull values from.

**Fix — set it in code-behind:**

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
    }
}
```

**Also ensure your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged`** (or inherits `ObservableObject` from the MVVM Community Toolkit) so the UI updates when properties change:

```csharp
public partial class MyViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string title = "Hello";

    [ObservableProperty]
    private string description = "World";
}
```

**TL;DR:** No `BindingContext` → bindings resolve to `null` → blank labels.
